Name: Cole-Carpenter syndrome
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta characterized by craniosynostosis

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 1
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that is characterized by bone fragility and blue sclerae and has_material_basis_in dominantly inherited mutations in the COL1A1 gene on chromosome 17q21.33 or the COL1A2 gene on chromosome 7q21.3.

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta with opalescent teeth
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta found in a single South African family.

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 8
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in mutation in the P3H1 gene on chromosome 1p34.2.

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 7
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in mutation in the CRTAP gene on chromosome 3p22.

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 17
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SPARC gene on chromosome 5q33.

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 3
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that is characterized by progressive limb and spinal deformity and normal sclerae and has_material_basis_in mutations in the COL1A1 gene on chromosome 17q21.33 or the COL1A2 gene on chromosome 7q21.3.
Synonym: progressively deforming osteogenesis imperfecta with normal sclera

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 4
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that is characterized by bone fragility and normal sclerae and has_material_basis_in dominantly inherited mutations in the COL1A1 gene on chromosome 17q21.33 or the COL1A2 gene on chromosome 7q21.3.

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 2
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that is characterized by bone fragility and perinatal lethality and has_material_basis_in dominantly inherited mutations in the COL1A1 gene on chromosome 17q21.33 or the COL1A2 gene on chromosome 7q21.3.

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 13
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in mutation in the BMP1 gene on chromosome 8p21.

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 14
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in mutation in the TMEM38B gene on chromosome 9q31.

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 5
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in mutation in the IFITM5 gene on chromosome 11p15.

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 16
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in contiguous gene deletion on chromosome 11p11.

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 10
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SERPINH gene on chromosome 11q13.

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 15
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in mutation in the WNT1 gene on chromosome 12q13.

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 12
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SP7 gene on chromosome 12q13.

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 9
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in mutation in the PPIB gene on chromosome 15q22.

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 6
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SERPINF1 gene on chromosome 17p13.3.

Name: osteogenesis imperfecta type 11
Definition: An osteogenesis imperfecta that has_material_basis_in mutation in the FKBP10 gene on chromosome 17q21.
